quote_last: (summer-time). Benson, my Aunt Agatha's butler, was offering me the fried potatoes at the moment, and such was my emotion that I lofted six of them on the sideboard with the spoon.
title: Sir Roderick Comes to Lunch
author: P.G. Wodehouse
